-{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-27T01:33:24.732Z","role":"user","content":"# Task T-003@20260427T001208Z: Implement `ModalClient` parallel implementation of `GenerationClient` Protocol.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- `client_modal.py` defines `ModalClient` satisfying `GenerationClient` Protocol<br/>- Uses Modal Python SDK to invoke a deployed MusicGen function<br/>- Cost computed from Modal prediction metadata × per-second A10G rate<br/>- Mocked test asserts Protocol parity with `ReplicateClient`<br/>- Real Modal call gated behind `@pytest.mark.live_modal` (skipped by default)\n\n**Tier:** T2 — Standard (New feature / moderate refactoring)\n\n## Instructions\n\nRead the project's ADP documentation and understand existing patterns before making changes.\n\n**ADP Phases:** Explore → Specify → Test → Implement → Verify → Document\n\n### Phase 0: Explore\n- Read all files in the affected area of the codebase.\n- Identify existing patterns, naming conventions, and architectural decisions.\n- Review related tests to understand expected behavior.\n- Update progress.md with exploration findings.\n\n### Phase 1: Specify\n- Write a specification to `specs/t-003@20260427t001208z-spec.md`.\n- Include: problem statement, technical approach, edge cases, acceptance criteria.\n- Each acceptance criterion must have a VERIFY command.\n\n### Phase 2: Test Development\n- Write tests BEFORE implementation, derived from the specification.\n- Tests must FAIL before implementation (Red phase).\n- After this phase, test files are LOCKED — do not modify assertions.\n\n### Phase 3: Implement\n- Implement the minimum code needed to pass all tests.\n- One sub-task at a time, commit each logical unit.\n- Type hints on all function signatures.\n- Follow existing patterns.\n\n### Phase 4: Verify & Document\n- Run full test suite and quality checks.\n- Update CHANGELOG.md, progress.md.\n\n## Rules\n\n- No questions — document assumptions in ESCALATIONS.md.\n- Do not modify locked test assertions.\n- Log new dependencies to ESCALATIONS.md.\n- Commit per sub-task: `feat(scope): summary [T-003@20260427T001208Z]`\n\n## Common Pitfalls (from recurring verify feedback)\n\nThese are the top reasons tasks get PASS WITH NOTES instead of clean PASS.\nAvoid them on the first attempt:\n\n- **Always include a migration** when adding or modifying database columns.\n  A new model or column without a migration is a deployment gap.\n- **Commit all changes** before the verify phase begins. Uncommitted work\n  is flagged as blocking by the verifier.\n- **Stay in scope** — only commit work under this task's ID. Do not bundle\n  changes from adjacent subtasks or refactor unrelated code.\n- **Add indexes on new FK columns** in `__table_args__` when adding\n  foreign key relationships.\n- **Keep CHANGELOG entries consistent** with actual behavior. Do not copy\n  descriptions from other tasks or specs without verifying they match\n  the implemented code.\n\n## Validation\n\nRun before final commit:\n```bash\npip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\n```\n\nAll must pass.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: [x] **Issue — severity: blocking**: New self-critique logic is not wired into the active composition pipeline. `my-claw/tools/senseweave/tracker_compiler.py` and `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py` continue to call `score_from_mood(...)` directly in piece generation; `revise_score(...)` from `senseweave.self_critique` is never imported or used by composition/playback flow..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Integrate the new `revise_score(...)` path into score generation before tracker/build or playback handoff (both gate-backed and fallback paths)..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that verifies a piece goes through critique/revision before being finalized for playback, with assertions that failed metrics can trigger one bounded rewrite attempt and that the final score is selected from the two-pass result..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Incomplete budget enforcement: budget fields for grain density, global density multiplier, LLM suppression, and DSP budget are computed but never applied in `tracker_solo_song`, so sample/grain and primary-form fallback is not actually enforced (`my-claw/tools/senseweave/resource_governor.py`, `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`). Severity: blocking..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Startup hardening gap: `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` does not call `bootstrap_identity()` before startup announcement and main loop, while this path is still part of the runnable daemon entry points (`my-claw/docs/PROJECT_GUIDE.md` and system scripts/tests reference it), so first-boot identity creation is not guaranteed in that mode. Severity: blocking..\n"}
