-{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T01:35:01.908Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777253701908_0","parameters":{"file_path":"specs/t-003@20260427t001208z-spec.md","content":"# Task T-003: Implement ModalClient\n\n## Problem Statement\nThe generation subsystem requires a parallel backend client to support rendering music using Modal (in addition to Replicate). The client must implement the `GenerationClient` Protocol (which currently takes a request and returns a result), compute cost using A10G rates and Modal prediction metadata, and include tests using a mocked Modal backend as well as a gated live test.\n\n## Technical Approach\n- Create `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py` defining `ModalClient`.\n- Implement `ModalClient` with an initialization signature and a `generate(request)` method.\n- Assume `GenerationRequest` and `GenerationResult` are duct-typed as `Any` for now to match the existing `client_replicate.py` stub, but return a struct/dataclass matching the expected `GenerationResult` shape or compute the cost internally and return it.\n- Use `modal.Function.lookup` (or equivalent Modal SDK primitives) to invoke the function.\n- Calculate cost: The A10G per-second rate will be applied to the function's execution time (metadata provided by Modal).\n- Create `tests/test_client_modal.py` to mock `modal.Function` and verify the protocol parity with `ReplicateClient` (both having a `generate(request)` method).\n- Create `tests/test_generation_live_modal.py` for the `@pytest.mark.live_modal` test.\n\n## Edge Cases\n- Modal function raises an exception (e.g., timeout, auth failure): should be caught and propagated cleanly, mirroring `GenerationError` if needed.\n- Prediction metadata might lack exact timing if the function fails early; cost should default to 0.0.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- `client_modal.py` defines `ModalClient` satisfying `GenerationClient` Protocol (via structural typing/duck-typing matching `ReplicateClient`)\n  - **VERIFY:** `python -c \"import inspect; from my_claw.tools.senseweave.generation.client_modal import ModalClient; from my_claw.tools.senseweave.generation.client_replicate import ReplicateClient; assert inspect.signature(ModalClient.generate) == inspect.signature(ReplicateClient.generate)\"`\n- Uses Modal Python SDK to invoke a deployed MusicGen function\n  - **VERIFY:** `grep -q \"modal.Function.lookup\" my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py`\n- Cost computed from Modal prediction metadata × per-second A10G rate\n  - **VERIFY:** `grep -q \"cost_usd\" my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py`\n- Mocked test asserts Protocol parity with `ReplicateClient`\n  - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_client_modal.py -v`\n- Real Modal call gated behind `@pytest.mark.live_modal` (skipped by default)\n  - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_generation_live_modal.py -v -m \"not live_modal\"`\n"}}
