building (`is_building=True`), the follower's amplitude is reduced and its contour apex is inverted to complement the leader.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- When the leader is pausing (`is_pausing=True`), the follower's amplitude is boosted and its contour apex is reinforced to fill the gap.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Role metadata (`leader`, `follower`, `solo`, `tacet`) is correctly parsed and respected, with the rule only applying to voices explicitly tagged as followers.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The task is complete according to the acceptance criteria:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `CallResponseRule` implemented in `render/rules/call_response.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Correct transformations for building and pausing states.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Metadata role parsing covers all required keys and values.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_call_response.py` verifies both functional behavior and role-based filtering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation is consistent with other \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tier 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" render rules in `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/` (e.g., `phrase_arch.py`, `articulation.py`). It uses the shared `Event` data model and follows the `role_is_eligible` contract established in `role_gate.py`. Although `PerformanceIntent` was mentioned in the spec, it is not yet present in the codebase (targeted for T-030), and the use of the `Event` model for these transformations is the correct adaptation for the current project state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+No security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were introduced. The implementation consists of pure-function mathematical transformations on local data structures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The code quality is high, with clear documentation, clean dataclass abstractions, and robust role-parsing logic. The tests use